17
00:02:25,420 --> 00:02:27,620
You will give my mother a most romantic wedding

18
00:02:31,380 --> 00:02:35,060
Ye, do you know where the pearl powder I bought is

19
00:02:35,140 --> 00:02:36,700
I have put it in the drawer

20
00:02:36,820 --> 00:02:38,180
Let me take it for you

21
00:02:44,420 --> 00:02:45,420
Help yourself

22
00:02:58,460 --> 00:03:05,860
[Thank you for holding my hand at that time]

23
00:03:08,700 --> 00:03:09,820
She doesn't even remember you?

24
00:03:10,260 --> 00:03:11,660
Sometimes she does

25
00:03:11,820 --> 00:03:14,380
She can only remember the time when I was born

26
00:03:15,140 --> 00:03:16,660
What does Lin Sen say?

27
00:03:16,860 --> 00:03:18,180
Why your mother forgot things suddenly?

28
00:03:18,540 --> 00:03:20,140
He has consulted many experts

29
00:03:20,580 --> 00:03:24,420
They said, with this disease it's very normal to result in confusion of memory

30
00:03:25,260 --> 00:03:27,900
My mother forgets many things

31
00:03:28,300 --> 00:03:31,580
but she remembers clearly the time when she got married with my father

32
00:03:32,100 --> 00:03:33,820
yezi, don't worry

33
00:03:34,260 --> 00:03:38,780
Lin Sen said that it would be help if your mother felt happy

34
00:03:39,020 --> 00:03:41,740
Right. So we need to focus on the wedding now

35
00:03:41,900 --> 00:03:43,140
Stop thinking about anything else

36
00:03:45,580 --> 00:03:46,940
Where is Zhuzi?

37
00:03:47,660 --> 00:03:49,340
I called her yesterday

38
00:03:49,460 --> 00:03:50,980
